Brace expansions :
  Brace expension is mechanism to generate arbitary string sharing a common prefix and suffix , either of which can be empty
  bash$ echo a{d,c,b}e
  ade ace abe

Shell parameter expansion: 
  The '$' character introduces parameter expansion, command substitution or airthmetic expansion. The basic form of parameter expansion is ${parameter}, which substitutes the value of parameter.
  $ string=01234567890abcdefgh
  $ echo ${string:7}
  7890abcdefgh
  
